.TH "batadv_nc_fwd_flush" 9 "batadv_nc_fwd_flush" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_nc_fwd_flush \- Checks the timestamp of the given nc packet.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_nc_fwd_flush
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_nc_path *nc_path "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_nc_packet *nc_packet "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "nc_path" 12
the nc path the packet belongs to
.IP "nc_packet" 12
the nc packet to be checked
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether the given nc packet has hit its forward timeout. If so, the
packet is no longer delayed, immediately sent and the entry deleted from the
queue. Has to be called with the appropriate locks.
.SH "RETURN"
false as soon as the entry in the fifo queue has not been timed out
yet and true otherwise.
